Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech in Indiana, highlighting the achievements of President Donald Trump's administration and discussing the need for tax cuts and the repeal of Obamacare. Pence praised Trump's leadership and commitment to putting America first. He also announced that Trump will be visiting Indiana to discuss his plan to boost the economy. Pence urged Congress to pass the Graham-Cassidy bill, which would repeal and replace Obamacare. He emphasized the need for a simpler and fairer tax code that would benefit working families and businesses. Pence called on the support of Indiana residents and encouraged them to voice their opinions on important issues facing the nation.